        <detaileddescription>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem>
<para>Any address bits of a memory or memory mapped register address for any read or write access on AXI or LMB. </para></listitem>
<listitem>
<para>Any data bits written to memory or a memory mapped register on AXI or LMB, as well as output on an AXI Stream. &lt; </para></listitem>
</itemizedlist>
</para><para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>InstancePtr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>is a pointer to the <ref refid="struct_x_t_m_r___inject" kindref="compound">XTMR_Inject</ref> instance. </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>Value</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>is the memory or register address, oro the data. </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>Mask</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>defines the bits where faults are injected. A fault is injected for every bit in the mask set to 1.</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>Either the unchanged value, or value with the faults injected for the CPU set up for fault injection.</para></simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>None. </para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
